<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://rafaelgreca.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://rafaelgreca.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2024-02-07T01:44:14+00:00</updated><id>https://rafaelgreca.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Rafael Greca’s personal website</title><subtitle>A simple, whitespace theme for academics. Based on [*folio](https://github.com/bogoli/-folio) design. </subtitle><entry><title type="html">How to deploy a machine learning model using Flask</title><link href="https://rafaelgreca.github.io/blog/2024/flask/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to deploy a machine learning model using Flask"/><published>2024-02-06T21:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-02-06T21:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://rafaelgreca.github.io/blog/2024/flask</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://rafaelgreca.github.io/blog/2024/flask/"><![CDATA[<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2> <p>“Flask is a <strong>lightweight</strong> WSGI web application framework. It is designed to make getting started quick and easy, with the ability to <strong>scale up to complex applications</strong>. It began as a simple wrapper around Werkzeug and Jinja and has become one of the <strong>most popular Python web application frameworks</strong>.” [1]</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/flask-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/flask-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/flask-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/flask.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <h2 id="notes">Notes</h2> <p>1) Importing the library:</p> <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="n">flask</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">Flask</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <p>2) Creating the Flask app:</p> <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">app</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nc">Flask</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">__name__</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <p>3) Creating the routes:</p> <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/train</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">GET</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">train</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">This endpoint will train the machine learning model</span><span class="sh">"</span>

<span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/inference</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">POST</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">inference</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">This endpoint will use the trained model to make an inference on the data</span><span class="sh">"</span>

<span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/incremental-learning</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">GET</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">incremental</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">This endpoint will increment the trained machine learning model</span><span class="sh">"</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <p>Difference between the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">GET</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">POST</code> methods [2]:</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/assets/img/comparison-get-post-480.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/assets/img/comparison-get-post-800.webp"/> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/assets/img/comparison-get-post-1400.webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/comparison-get-post.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <p>4) Running the Flask app:</p> <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">__name__</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">__main__</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">app</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">run</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">0.0.0.0</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">debug</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <p>5) Full example:</p> <div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="n">flask</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">Flask</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="n">flask</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">request</span> <span class="c1"># to get the data that was sent
</span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="n">flask</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">jsonify</span> <span class="c1"># to transform the endpoint's output in a json
</span>
<span class="n">app</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nc">Flask</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">__name__</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/train</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">POST</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">train</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="sh">"""</span><span class="s">
    This endpoint will train the machine learning model.
    </span><span class="sh">"""</span>
    <span class="c1"># get the data that will be used to train the model
</span>    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">request</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">json</span>

    <span class="c1"># train the model
</span>    <span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">train_model</span><span class="p">()</span>

    <span class="c1"># calculate the model's metrics and returns a dict
</span>    <span class="n">model_metrics</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">get_metrics</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nf">jsonify</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model_metrics</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/inference</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">POST</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">inference</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="sh">"""</span><span class="s">
    This endpoint will use the trained model to make an inference on the data.
    </span><span class="sh">"""</span>
    <span class="c1"># get the data that will be used to test the model
</span>    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">request</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">json</span>

    <span class="c1"># inference (returns a dict)
</span>    <span class="n">predictions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">make_predictions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nf">jsonify</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">predictions</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nd">@app.route</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">/incremental-learning</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">methods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">POST</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">incremental</span><span class="p">():</span>    
    <span class="sh">"""</span><span class="s">
    This endpoint will increment the trained machine learning model.
    </span><span class="sh">"""</span>
    <span class="c1"># get the data that will be used to increment the trained model
</span>    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">request</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">json</span>

    <span class="c1"># increment the model
</span>    <span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">increment_model</span><span class="p">()</span>

    <span class="c1"># calculate the new model's metrics and returns a dict
</span>    <span class="n">model_metrics</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">get_metrics</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nf">jsonify</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">model_metrics</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">__name__</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">__main__</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">app</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nf">run</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="s">0.0.0.0</span><span class="sh">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">debug</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div> <p>6) How access the endpoints using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">CURL</code>:</p> <p><strong>POST</strong>:</p> <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>curl <span class="nt">-X</span> POST http://127.0.0.1:&lt;PORT&gt;/&lt;ENDPOINT&gt; <span class="nt">-H</span> <span class="s1">'Content-Type: application/json'</span> <span class="se">\</span>
     <span class="nt">-H</span> <span class="s1">'Accept: application/json'</span> <span class="nt">-d</span> &lt;JSON_DATA&gt;
</code></pre></div></div> <p><strong>GET</strong>:</p> <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>curl <span class="nt">-X</span> GET http://127.0.0.1:&lt;PORT&gt;/&lt;ENDPOINT&gt;
</code></pre></div></div> <h2 id="references">References</h2> <p>[1] https://github.com/pallets/flask [2] https://www.w3schools.com/tags/ref_httpmethods.asp</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="flask"/><category term="model-deployment"/><category term="study-notes"/><category term="flask"/><category term="model-deployment"/><category term="study-notes"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[My study notes about how to deploy a machine learning model using Flask.]]></summary></entry></feed>